strong.span: COVID-19 UPDATE: Information is coming quickly and changing hourly.

span.br: On behalf of the Clark County Health Department, the following information is being shared:

p.span: Today, March 17, 2020 Governor Laura Kelly announced all school facilities will be closed for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. This will place tremendous hardship on our families and staff, and impact the social and emotional well-being of our students.
We have been working with KSDE on a contingency plan, including how we can meet the ongoing learning needs of our students and provide breakfast and lunch for our students.
March 23-27 – USD 220 staff will begin developing a “continuous learning plan” for our students.

USD 220 will continue to provide food service for all students as previously noted. Please use the link to request breakfast and lunch during regular school days. Link: https://forms.gle/1sRX9zx2jgf8voYb7

Our staff and board of education are also working on other critical issues, such as what this means for our seniors, how this will affect next school year and what impact this will have on our employees. We will provide updates on these issues as soon as the information is available.

We are committed to working together as a community to support one another throughout these unprecedented times, and communication will remain a top priority. This will include updates we receive from the Kansas State Department of Education, Kansas Department of Health & Environment, and any other governmental agency. We will continue to post information on our social media platforms (Facebook & Twitter), school website (www.usd220.net), as well as use go.edustar to send emails to parents.
As a reminder, this school closure is in response to the current public health crisis. The focus should remain on preventing the spread the coronavirus, or COVID-19 as it is also referred to.
Please be mindful of the following:

li.style: color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:; font-size: 11pt; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; vertical-align: baseline;

li.span: Avoid close contact with anyone with cold or flu-like symptoms.

br.span: Ashland is the largest city in and the county seat of Clark County, Kansas. Ashland lies along what was once a military road from Fort Dodge to the north and Fort Supply to the south (located fifty miles south of Dodge City).
USD 220 serves the communities of Ashland, Englewood, and the surrounding area. Ashland High School competes within the KSHSAA 1A classification.
and our teachers are on a 166-day contract. We have a 96% attendance rate and 95-100% graduation rate. USD 220 has well-maintained buildings and grounds and the latest classroom technology.

span.style: color: rgb(23, 54, 93); font-family: "Century Schoolbook"; font-style: italic;

br.span: The Mission of USD 220, is to develop learning skills in every student that will provide the necessary background to enable each student to find success and fulfillment in a constantly changing world.
